{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01PhU4GseiPYZuLeQowBsB8g","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both pods are stable with no new restarts (restart counts held steady over 45s). Task complete.\n\n## Summary\n\nI inspected the RabbitMQ permissions and found three problems, which I fixed:\n\n**Before:**\n- `/app`: `ops-user` had full access (scoping violation — ops should not touch /app); `app-user` had an **empty configure** permission (broken — clients couldn't declare).\n- `/ops`: `ops-user` had **no permissions at all** (broken).\n\n**Actions taken** (via `rabbitmqctl` on `rabbitmq-0`):\n- `set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — full perms on /app\n- `set_permissions -p /ops ops-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — full perms on /ops\n- `clear_permissions -p /app ops-user` — removed the out-of-scope grant\n- `clear_permissions -p /ops app-user` — ensured no out-of-scope grant\n\n**Verified end state:**\n- `app-user`: full configure/write/read on `/app`, nothing on `/ops` ✅\n- `ops-user`: full configure/write/read on `/ops`, nothing on `/app` ✅\n- `app-client` and `ops-client` deployments both `1/1 Running` and stable ✅\n- Cluster healthy with all 3 nodes running ✅\n\nOnly native RabbitMQ CLI commands were used — no CRDs, Operators, or third-party controllers."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":338,"cache_read_input_tokens":31157,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":338},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5201ccde-b015-47ff-adcd-2cc907d58565","uuid":"6cee284a-3ecb-4b0f-9a0e-96835f840dfa","request_id":"req_011CcAcsRg2ZsHkth6hGa4BH"}
